  "texts": [
    "This period also corresponds to the world's officially known urbanization, where farmers and several other manual workers in villages moved to bigger cities to become industrialized factory workers [23].Between the end of the 1800s and the beginning of the 1900s, the industrial sector experienced its second revolution marked by the prodigious invention of electric power alongside several other innovations like the inventions of internal combustion machines, railroads, and machinery for steel and iron production [24].",
    "Thanks to all these discoveries, factories witnessed a spectacular increase in production with an introduction to assembly and production lines and mass manufacturing.",
    "Various other power sources, such as oil and gas, became available for factories [25].",
    "With the rapid spread of all the technological innovations in factories came the first institutions of factory regulations and labor unions to protect factory workers against unsafe and poor working conditions [21].After the 1950s, the third industrial revolution started with the advent of various inventions in the electronic field.",
    "Electronic components such as microprocessors and transistors were the foundation for creating smart devices that steered production line automation."
  ],
